name: Freud
overview: Eager to make his name in 19th-century Vienna, a hungry young Sigmund Freud joins a psychic and an inspector to solve a string of bloody mysteries.

episodes.name: Hysteria
episodes.overview: Struggling with his career and swigging cocaine, Freud is pulled into a gruesome crime, then into an exclusive séance led by a mesmerizing psychic.

episodes.name: Trauma
episodes.overview: His theories opposed, Freud tips off authorities searching for a lost innocent. But he’ll have to collaborate with an outsider to get to the truth.

episodes.name: Somnambul
episodes.overview: A duel takes a startling turn, with dire consequences. Sophia plants deadly seeds, a dreamer awakens and Freud learns how to unlock a shuttered mind.

episodes.name: Totem and Taboo
episodes.overview: Wishes — and nightmares — do come true as Freud teeters on the brink of self-destruction and Sophia and Viktor realize their deepest desires.

episodes.name: Desire
episodes.overview: Roused from a terrifying dream yet unable to shake a living nightmare, Fleur struggles with Freud. Killers close in as a bottomless rage spills forth.

episodes.name: Regression
episodes.overview: The effects of trauma run deeper than even Freud suspected as he looks into a dead pianist. Viktor accepts an invitation, and Kiss confronts Heinz.

episodes.name: Catharsis
episodes.overview: Desperate to hide the truth, Freud takes refuge in the haunted flat. A curse is sealed, and all must face their worst fears as the darkness closes in.

episodes.name: Suppression
episodes.overview: An empire comes under siege from within as an inner circle upends the establishment. Once a door is opened, can it ever really be closed?
